---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const frontmatter = {
  title: "Best Practices for User Management in 2024",
  description: "Learn how to effectively manage user roles and permissions in modern applications.",
  date: "2024-03-10",
  author: "Michael Rodriguez",
  category: "Tutorials",
  image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80"
};
---

<Layout title={frontmatter.title}>
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <header class="text-center mb-16">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
            <span class="gradient-text">{frontmatter.title}</span>
          </h1>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
            <time datetime={frontmatter.date}>{new Date(frontmatter.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}</time>
            <span>•</span>
            <span>{frontmatter.category}</span>
            <span>•</span>
            <span>{frontmatter.author}</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
          <img 
            src={frontmatter.image} 
            alt={frontmatter.title}
            class="w-full rounded-2xl mb-12 aspect-[2/1] object-cover"
          />

          <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            As applications become more complex and security threats more sophisticated, implementing robust user management strategies is crucial for protecting your digital ecosystem.
          </p>

          <section class="my-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 gradient-text">Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</h2>
            <p>
              Implement granular role-based access control to ensure users have precisely the permissions they need. This principle of least privilege minimizes potential security risks and streamlines user management.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="my-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 gradient-text">Key Best Practices</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Use multi-factor authentication for enhanced security</li>
              <li>Implement dynamic permission hierarchies</li>
              <li>Regularly audit and update user roles</li>
              <li>Leverage single sign-on (SSO) technologies</li>
              <li>Encrypt sensitive user data at rest and in transit</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="my-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 gradient-text">Modern Authentication Strategies</h2>
            <p>
              Embrace modern authentication protocols like OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect. These standards provide robust, scalable solutions for managing user identities across complex application ecosystems.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="mt-12 text-center">
            <a href="/blog" class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
              Back to Our Blogs
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>